    "game-obj": "Weapons",
    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "weapon",
        "text": "This long metal pole has a large chakram attached at the end. A mechanism within the handle allows the wielder to launch and retract the chakram, which is connected with wire to the inside of the weapon. The donchak is seldom seen used outside training scenarios.",
        "level": 0,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Uncommon",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 159,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
                "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "uncommon"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Hampering",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 344,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core 2",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
                            "alt": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 227
                        },
                        "page": 274,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "1.1",
                            "alt": "1.1",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 227
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "b1653a2560569e642d9a2dc5c42acf5a",
                "text": "A weapon with the hampering trait includes a disruptive limb or flange. After you hit with the weapon, you can use an Interact action to give the target a \u201310-foot circumstance penalty to all Speeds. The penalty ends after the target takes a move action, at the start of your next turn, if you attack with the weapon, or if you move out of reach of the target, whichever comes first.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Interact",
                        "alt": "Interact",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 2297
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "move",
                        "alt": "move",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 658
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Reach",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 192,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 283",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 283",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 283,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "1d6143e399ba5d4085ca236a97cf860c",
                "text": "This weapon can be used to attack enemies up to 10 feet away instead of only adjacent enemies. For creatures with reach, the weapon increases their reach by 5 feet.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Reload",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "legacy",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Core Rulebook",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 279",
                            "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 279",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        },
                        "page": 279,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "4.0",
                            "alt": "4.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "15577d9931e0c744a9e12be2d087a290",
                "text": "While all weapons need some amount of time to get into position, many ranged weapons also need to be loaded and reloaded. This entry indicates how many Interact actions it takes to reload such weapons. This can be 0 if drawing ammunition and firing the weapon are part of the same action. If an item takes 2 or more actions to reload, the GM determines whether they must be performed together as an activity, or you can spend some of those actions during one turn and the rest during your next turn.  \n  \nAn item with an entry of \u201c\u2014\u201d must be drawn to be thrown, which usually takes an Interact action just like drawing any other weapon. Reloading a ranged weapon and drawing a thrown weapon both require a free hand. Switching your grip to free a hand and then to place your hands in the grip necessary to wield the weapon are both included in the actions you spend to reload a weapon.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ],
                "value": "1"
            },
            {
                "name": "Tethered",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 252,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core 2",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
                            "alt": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 227
                        },
                        "page": 274,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "1.1",
                            "alt": "1.1",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 227
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "93ab405e7b3b5a2c09d54871ceacfe40",
                "text": "This weapon is attached to a length of rope or chain that allows you to retrieve it after it has left your hand. If you have a free hand (including if you've just thrown a two-handed tethered weapon and have a hand holding nothing but the weapon's tether), you can use an Interact action to pull the weapon back into your grasp after you have thrown it as a ranged attack or after it has been disarmed (unless it's being held by another creature).",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Interact",
                        "alt": "Interact",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 2297
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "disarmed",
                        "alt": "disarmed",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 2383
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Thrown",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 195,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 283",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 283",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 283,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "c42503980965022311443a6e1e55ab57",
                "text": "You can throw this weapon as a ranged attack; it is a ranged weapon when thrown. You add your Strength modifier to damage as you would for a melee weapon. When this trait appears on a melee weapon, it also includes the range increment. Ranged weapons with this trait use the range increment in the weapon\u2019s Range entry.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ],
                "value": "20 ft."
            }
        ],
